# Cloudflare Pages redirects / SPA fallback.
#
# Pages serves static files first: an exact match, then `<path>/index.html`,
# then `<path>.html`. Our prerender writes BOTH `dist/recipes/<slug>/index.html`
# and `dist/recipes/<slug>.html` so clean URLs resolve to the prerendered file
# without any rewrite needed — Googlebot sees the per-route <title>, meta and
# Recipe JSON-LD in the initial HTML response.
#
# Only routes that DON'T have a prerendered file (dynamic admin pages, auth,
# 404s, etc.) fall through to this rule and load the React SPA shell. The 200
# status code is required so the SPA route handler can take over client-side.

